1. Find a piece of satire - either TV show, article or movie ~ Australian is preferable but American and British satire is fine (As long as your audience understands it!)

Use the following analysis questions and write a two paragraph analysis of the text.

-   Who/What is the subject of the satire?
-   What is the key issue that is being revealed in this satirical piece? (Research needed)
-   What is the purpose of this satire? - What change does the author want to see?
-   What other literary techniques have been used? e.g. foreshadowing, metaphor, exaggeration, ridicule, irony, symbolism. Explain and use evidence.
-   How does the author use other techniques in this satirical text? e.g film techniques
-   What type of Satire is this? Explain why and use evidence.

PARAGRAPH STRUCTURE

1. Topic sentence

2. Elaboration / Explain further

3. Evidence (2-3 pieces of evidence needed)

4. Analysis (You will need to analyse each piece of evidence)

5. Closing sentence

So, where do you find a piece of satire?

-   Go to the Module titled "Examples of Satire". There you will find links to a number of satrical sites/programs etc.
-   Go to ABC Iview - Black Comedy, Sammy J and Mark Humphries
-   Find your own piece of satire
-   You don't have to choose a show, you can read a satirical article and analyse this.
